In recent months, we've been receiving an increasing amount of submissions from readers (thanks!) and while we use many of them, we don't have enough time to review everything to the right level. Given the backlog, we want to try out a new section to share things from our inbox to you more quickly: Golgi by Rob Tweed is an interesting take on a UI framework built around Web Components and with no build steps required. Maxim Orlov has written about how to run concurrent tasks within a defined limit using purely JavaScript. spotify-mini is a Node wrapper around Spotify's Web API. neo.mjs (which has just hit version 4.0) is a performance-oriented framework built around workers and its team is continuing to implement cool looking stuff. If you have something to submit, email jsw@peterc.org or just hit reply to any issue of this newsletter and we'll see it :-)
